race.comment: WAKU WAKU (20) is lightly raced but is yet to miss the top-four in five starts to date and looks the runner in this field with the most upside. Maps perfectly for this from gate three and gets in on the minimum weight. Should be right there at the business end. SENESCHAL (5) is a last-start winner who has placed two of three around this circuit and gets 3kg off with the claim. Ticks a few boxes for a race like this. TRAPEDO (15) is two from two over this course and distance and will strip fitter third-up from the spell. Makes plenty of appeal. SHE OURS (13) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and may earn some minor money again. HEYOKA (10) doesn't know how to put in a poor one and will run her usual honest race.
